# ============================================================================
# .gitignore — aap_config
# ============================================================================

# Ansible — collections installed from collections/requirements.yml.
# They install into the container/runner ~/.ansible, but ignore a local copy
# too in case anyone installs with `-p collections/`.
collections/ansible_collections/

# Ansible — local cache dirs created by ansible / ansible-lint.
.ansible/

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Secrets — never commit. Two complementary secret channels, both gitignored:
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1) Connection secrets sourced into the shell. Real file is
#    gitignored; the committed template is docs/dev-environment.sh.example
#    (different filename, NOT matched). No leading slash — matches in any dir.
dev-environment.sh

# 2) Vault password files used to encrypt config/*/secrets.yml.
.vault_pass
.vault_password
*.vault_pass
.vault-password
*.vault-password

# Raw OAuth tokens, if any ever get written to disk.
*.token

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Exports — raw filetree_create output. The tree IS committed for review and
# history, BUT *_settings exports can embed SSO/client secrets that
# secrets_as_variables does not template out — so those are excluded and the
# trainee curates them by hand (runbook 03).
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
exports/**/*_settings*
exports/**/*settings*.yaml
exports/**/*settings*.yml

# Claude Code per-project state (memory, transcripts, settings) — ignored,
# EXCEPT repo-shipped skills, which are part of the kit.
.claude/*
!.claude/skills/

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
